        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/editor_top_basic.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Inside the frame, you find a number of tabs and buttons.</para>
        <para>The input forms are organised into a numbers of tab-sets. To access the Basic Input Forms, open the editor. 
            This tab divides into three subtabs, one for "Publication", one for "Container", and one for "Contents".</para>
        <para>Clicking on the button above the tabs to the left takes you to a new set of tabs. The next tab is called "Citation Forms" and the next "Content Description Forms." The last set of tabs is called "Remaining Forms." 
            This label covers a number of fields mainly of administrative interest and fields as the "Note" field, the "Related Items" fields and the "Identifiers". </para>
        <para>The button then completes the circle and allows you to go back to the Basic Input Forms.</para>
        <para>"Citation Forms," "Content Description Forms" and "Remaining Forms" cover the same ground as the Basic Input Forms, only in more detail, offering more specialised input options.</para>
